; Coverage for amount.cc line 213:
; When a time-colon amount (h or m commodity) with COMMODITY_STYLE_THOUSANDS
; has more than 3 integer digits, the thousands separator should be a colon
; instead of a comma. Input uses comma-thousands to set the style flag.

2024/01/01 * Work
    (Billable:Client)    1,234.50h

2024/01/02 * Work
    (Billable:Client)    2,345.50h

test bal --time-colon
           3:580:00h  Billable:Client
end test
